    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-11-06T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-11-06T13:00:00-05:00" n="764"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d764">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/11–650: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Douglas</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to <gloss type="to">the Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-11-06T18:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 6, 1950—6 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 6—4:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2623. Text Secretary’s message to Bevin (Deptel 2344, November 6 repeated <gloss
                        target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> 478) as forwarded via British Embassy,
                    received <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> 11 a. m. today. <gloss
                        target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> has drafted telegram to Washington
                    stating (1) UK accepts U.S. resolution on Chinese intervention (Deptel 477 to
                        <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> repeated London 2343)<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d764fn1">November 5, 11 p. m., to New York, <ref target="#pg_1049"
                            >p. 1049</ref>.</note> with slight modifications and will be co-sponsor,
                    and (2) Bevin will reply separately to Secretary’s message as soon as it can be
                    carefully studied.</p>
                <p>Department pass <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> as London 43.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Douglas</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
